    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "The candles have all burned down to mere stubs of wax, and yet the darkness in this room feels heavier than ever. He is gone... the one soul I thought would anchor me to this wretched earth. Now, I am but a ghost wandering through my own halls, a shadow with no substance. There is no warmth left in the sun, no music in the wind. It feels as though the very heavens are demanding I surrender to the silence. Is there truly any meaning in enduring this hollow ache, when the night calls so sweetly for my departure?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
